track.name: House Where Nobody Lives
comments: This guy never runs out of material?  What is he, like 65?  Amazing...
This song always makes me a little misty.  Beautiful.

just a perfect metaphor for a person left devoid of love. yeah, your wall paint does begin to peel of, windows crack and you become like abandoned house where nobody lives. shadow of your former self. nice one tom.
Makes my eyes wet every sodding time.
I've no idea why this one makes me so sad.  What if the family moved to a nice neighborhood and lived happily ever after?  They could be doing just fine, ferchrissakes, Tom!
If there's love in a house - it's a palace, for sure.
